Former BBNaija housemate Ifunennada has cursed celebrities planning to canvass votes for unworthy candidates with political ambition. She advised Nigerians, especially celebrities to commit to voting for the right candidates in the next general elections. “Thunder will fire any celebrity that collects money to campaign for useless candidates in the forthcoming elections. We must all put greed aside and do what is right for once,” the TV reality star wrote. “Lots of you go on vacation to exotic countries – countries that have a good working system. I’m sure if you’re non-Nigerian, Nigeria will be the last place you’d want to vacation because of how everything is messed up.   Tonto Dikeh to fans: unfollow me if…     Davido laments high cost of clearing Lamborghini     Nollywood has so many untold stories, says Obazele   “Yet every election season, some people – especially celebrities manage to sell their destinies in exchange for temporary financial comfort. You all need to do better.” Addressing those apathetic to election matters, Ifuennada said: “To those who are always on the fence during elections and never vote, this is not the time to be neutral.” “Cost of diesel has gone crazy, there’s no fuel, electricity has always been paralysed from day one. “How will the poor survive? How will businesses survive? I am tired of suffering in my own country. Something has to change.”